  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Sustainable Ways of Life in Piura&apos;s Dry Forest Communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The small farmers that live in poverty and have limited resources to increase their productivity. Their agriculture and silviculture (tree farming) production systems are vulnerable to drought cycles. Additionally the families are bereft of social assistance as the state does not take this area into account in their plans and programs. Approximately 5000 families from these small-scale farming communities will participate in the project bettering their quality of life through improved agroecological production systems enhanced diet and increased income as well as by having their development needs addressed by the government. A total of 1000 original families will receive sheep goats ducks bees seeds irrigation systems improved cooking stoves training and technical assistance. These same families will Pass on the Gift to 1500 additional families. Training and technical assistance will be passed on to another 2500 families. Through the project all of the families will improve their well-being and achieve regional recognition of their organization and commitment to food sovereignty.</narrative>
  </description>
